Morgan Stanley said its first-quarter profit fell 9% from a year ago, hit by the same trading slump early in the year that hurt other Wall Street firms.

The bank posted a profit of $2.4 billion, or $1.39 a share, on revenue of $10.3 billion. Both are lower than the same period a year earlier, when the firm earned $2.7 billion, or $1.45 a share, on record quarterly revenue of $11.1 billion.

